How to Load the Database and Tables?

Before we begin the SQL Challenge we first need to load the files into SQL. We have already done this step and have created a database for it. Please click the zip file provided in the data file and load it into SQL Server. Do this by first extracting the zip files contents and then opening the file in Management Studios. The file should look something like the image below.

 Now you can click the execute button located at the top bar menu marked with the red exclamation mark. To clarify the button is highlighted in the image below.

Once that is done the Database called SQL Challenge should appear in the Object Explorer with three tables inside of it. Check the Object Explorer window on the left panel and first refresh the page then look for the database called SQL Challenge and click the button to expand it and do the same for the Tables menu. Under the Tables menu, you should see three tables: accounts, revenue_invoice_info, and users. The image below displays the steps sequentially. 


After checking for the tables we can now proceed to answer the challenge questions. 

For more information on how to load a database file into SQL Server look into this website:

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7828060/how-do-i-import-a-sql-data-file-into-sql-server
